{
  "texts": [
    "As shown, Infinity [21] takes 2.115 seconds per inference while scale-travel takes slightly longer at 2.638 seconds per inference.",
    "Similarly, Switti [66] achieves an inference time of 1.642 seconds, which increases modestly to 1.892 seconds when combined with scale-travel.",
    "Notably, this corresponds to only a 15% overhead, while yielding substantial improvements in the diversity-quality trade-off.",
    "The plot shows the result of different schedulers applied to CFG scheduling.",
    "We find that constant CFG scheduling yields the best results.)."
  ]
}